  <h2>3. Data Storage and Security</h2>

  <h3>3.1 Dual Database Architecture</h3>
  <p>We maintain a dual database system:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Airtable:</strong> Primary data storage for user interface and content management</li>
    <li><strong>PostgreSQL:</strong> Secondary storage on Railway for advanced features and redundancy</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3.2 Security Measures</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> OAuth tokens and sensitive data are encrypted using AES-256-CBC</li>
    <li><strong>Password Security:</strong> Passwords are hashed using bcryptjs with salt rounds</li>
    <li><strong>Secure Transmission:</strong> All data transmitted via HTTPS/TLS</li>
    <li><strong>Access Controls:</strong> JWT-based authentication with expiring tokens</li>
    <li><strong>Rate Limiting:</strong> Protection against abuse and automated attacks</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3.3 Data Retention</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Account Data:</strong> Retained while your account is active</li>
    <li><strong>Video Content:</strong> Stored until you remove it or close your account</li>
    <li><strong>Generated Content:</strong> Retained for the duration of your subscription</li>
    <li><strong>Logs:</strong> Technical logs retained for 90 days for security and debugging</li>
  </ul>

